        <div class="pageTitle">Recording Fee Schedule</div>

        <div class="infoBox">
            Fees are established by Grand Duchy Ordinance No. 1374-B and are subject to change by proclamation of the Arcane Council. All fees are payable in Gold Sovereigns (GP) or equivalent assayed coin at the time of filing. The ROD does not accept Plump Helmets, cave wheat, or promissory notes as payment.
            For step-by-step instructions on preparing and submitting each document type, see the <a href="/l1/taxes/how-to">How To Guides</a>.
            To search existing recorded instruments, use <a href="/l1/taxes/tax-search">Tax Search</a>.
        </div>

        <div class="formSection">
            <strong>Standard Document Recording Fees</strong>

            <table class="aspNetTable" style="width: 95%; margin-top: 10px;">
                <tr>
                    <th style="width: 80px;">Index Type</th>
                    <th>Document Type</th>
                    <th style="width: 120px;">Base Fee (1st page)</th>
                    <th style="width: 130px;">Each Add'l Page</th>
                    <th style="width: 120px;">Max Fee</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DEED</td>
                    <td>Warranty Deed, Quitclaim Deed, Trustee's Deed, Sheriff's Deed</td>
                    <td>15.00 GP</td>
                    <td>2.00 GP</td>
                    <td>75.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>MTG</td>
                    <td>Mortgage, Purchase Money Mortgage, Construction Mortgage</td>
                    <td>25.00 GP</td>
                    <td>2.00 GP</td>
                    <td>125.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>LIEN</td>
                    <td>Claim of Mechanic's Lien, Construction Lien, Judgment Lien</td>
                    <td>10.00 GP</td>
                    <td>2.00 GP</td>
                    <td>50.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>ESMT</td>
                    <td>Grant of Easement, Easement Agreement, Utility Easement</td>
                    <td>15.00 GP</td>
                    <td>2.00 GP</td>
                    <td>75.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ASGN</td>
                    <td>Assignment of Mortgage, Assignment of Lien, Partial Assignment</td>
                    <td>20.00 GP</td>
                    <td>2.00 GP</td>
                    <td>60.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>REL</td>
                    <td>Release of Lien, Satisfaction of Mortgage, Discharge of Judgment</td>
                    <td>10.00 GP</td>
                    <td>2.00 GP</td>
                    <td>30.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>NTC</td>
                    <td>Notice of Commencement, Amended NOC, Notice of Termination</td>
                    <td>10.00 GP</td>
                    <td>2.00 GP</td>
                    <td>30.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>AFF</td>
                    <td>Affidavit of Title, Affidavit of Heirship, Correction Affidavit</td>
                    <td>10.00 GP</td>
                    <td>2.00 GP</td>
                    <td>30.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>

        <div class="formSection">
            <strong>Supplemental & Miscellaneous Fees</strong>

            <table class="aspNetTable" style="width: 95%; margin-top: 10px;">
                <tr>
                    <th>Service</th>
                    <th style="width: 140px;">Fee</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Certified copy of recorded instrument (per copy)</td>
                    <td>5.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>Uncertified / plain copy (per page)</td>
                    <td>1.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Expedited same-day recording surcharge</td>
                    <td>50.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>ROD Cover Sheet (form ELD-CVR), if not self-prepared</td>
                    <td>2.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Notice to Owner (form ELD-NTO-01) filing</td>
                    <td>5.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>Index search (per name, per 10-year period)</td>
                    <td>3.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Parcel history report (all instruments on a single parcel)</td>
                    <td>15.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>Rejection / re-submission handling fee (per returned instrument)</td>
                    <td>5.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Judicial release recording (court order in lieu of satisfaction)</td>
                    <td>15.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>Late satisfaction penalty (Eldoria Code §44-B, per month of delay)</td>
                    <td>100.00 GP</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>

        <div class="formSection">
            <strong>Transfer Tax</strong><br><br>
            <span class="aspNetLabel">
                A subterranean property transfer tax is assessed on all conveyancing instruments (DEED index type)
                at the rate of <strong>0.5 GP per 100 GP</strong> of consideration, rounded up to the nearest whole sovereign.
                Transfer tax is collected at the time of recording and is separate from the recording fee.
                Instruments reciting nominal consideration (e.g., trust transfers, intra-family conveyances)
                must attach a completed Declaration of Consideration (form ELD-TC-01) or the full tax rate
                of <strong>2.0 GP per 100 GP</strong> of assessed value will apply.
            </span>

            <table class="aspNetTable" style="width: 60%; margin-top: 10px;">
                <tr>
                    <th>Consideration Range</th>
                    <th>Transfer Tax Rate</th>
                    <th>Example Tax</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>0 – 500.00 GP</td>
                    <td>0.5 GP per 100 GP</td>
                    <td>2.50 GP on 500 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>500.01 – 5,000.00 GP</td>
                    <td>0.5 GP per 100 GP</td>
                    <td>25.00 GP on 5,000 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>5,000.01 – 50,000.00 GP</td>
                    <td>0.5 GP per 100 GP</td>
                    <td>250.00 GP on 50,000 GP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="alternatingRow">
                    <td>50,000.01 GP and above</td>
                    <td>0.75 GP per 100 GP</td>
                    <td>750.00 GP on 100,000 GP</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>

        <div class="formSection">
            <strong>Payment Methods Accepted</strong><br><br>
            <span class="aspNetLabel">
                The ROD accepts the following forms of payment at the public counter (Room 230):<br><br>
                &bull; Gold Sovereigns (exact change preferred; the ROD maintains limited coinage reserves)<br>
                &bull; Certified Vault Draft drawn on a Grand Duchy-chartered financial institution<br>
                &bull; Institutional Account Voucher (pre-approved law firms and title companies only)<br><br>
                <strong>Not accepted:</strong> Copper Coins (must be exchanged at the Mountainhome Assay Office prior to filing),
                Elven scrip, Goblin trade tokens, Forgotten Beast hides, raw gemstones, or any form of arcane barter.
            </span>
        </div>

